<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-13T13:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-13T13:36:00-05:00" n="475" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 814.48/65</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Leavell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-13T12:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 13, 1918, noon.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Joint Committee of American and Guatemalan Red Cross are endeavoring to
                            arrange program of operations to clean city of filth which the President
                            promises put through. Unless this is done thoroughly and promptly,
                            disastrous epidemics are inevitable, for all open spaces are jammed and
                            the people are without necessary conveniences.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Leavell</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>